{
  "doc_id": "22115",
  "text": "The inclusion of the MS guidelines for adults was in response to the growing evidence base showing that higher levels of muscle strength are associated with a reduced risk of premature mortality and cardiovascular disease across all ages, independent of aerobic PA levels [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . There are also metabolic benefits to undertaking regular MS activities, such as improved insulin action, blood glucose control, and fat oxidation, all of which are critical in the prevention and treatment of type 2 diabetes and metabolic syndrome [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . There is tentative evidence to suggest MS activities improve self-esteem [CITATION_6] , and ameliorate symptoms of depression and anxiety [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
